<BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Friends/LilKegger.gif WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is &quot;Hazapet&quot; a sentence? (please read)</span><hr size=1> In the naming policy there's a section relating to the phonetics of the name, if it sounds like a word that would make a sentence or a title then it's not allowed. <p><TABLE BORDER="0">	<TR><TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><B>EverQuest</B><BR>		<A NAME="">Hethral Kegslayer</A> - Dwarven Templar<BR>		<A NAME="">Hethrael Hethralkin</A> - Dwarven Champion<BR>		<I><A HREF="http://www.etherealknighthood.com/index.shtml">Ethereal Knighthood</A></I><BR>		<A HREF="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis">Brell Serilis</A>	</TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroguemotoko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rogue Motoko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 1:39:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is &quot;Hazapet&quot; a sentence? (please read)</span><hr size=1> Most GMs or Guides only petition a name themselves if it's too offensive or a clear violation they can't let go without coming over as playing favorites for allowing it.  But in general I think most name changes come to existance because someone petitioned a name.  They can't ignore it if it's petitioned.  <br><br>But this is all speculation off course as I don't know the inner workings of Guides or how their brain works. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhorenstonefall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khoren Stonefall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elven Lovepony</span><br>  Posts: 1266<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 6:07:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/jmlong/khoren_little.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is &quot;Hazapet&quot; a sentence? (please read)</span><hr size=1> Yes, Oeln Hazapet forms a sentence.  I've sorta suspected for a long time that one day I'd read that your last name was taken away.  Sorry to hear about it, 'cause no one likes to lose their name, but every time I saw it, I realized it was living on borrowed time.<br><br>It's violation of the 11th and 13th parts of the naming policy was clear.  You can disagree with the policy, but it's not right to fault the GM for enforcing it, since that's their job.  <br><br>And as for why it managed to stay this long:  Enforcement is often not immediate or absolute, but the threat of it is what's supposed to keep people from being in violation of a rule in the first place.  I've also been caught speeding and had the cop decide not to give me a ticket, maybe 'cause he thought I was a nice guy.  But that $337 ticket I got a few years ago taught me not rely on that always happening.<br><br>We just rarely complain when people fail to do their jobs, and in failing to do so benefit us. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Khoren Stonefall<br>Level 60 Crusader of Marr<br>Silent 