otted you its lights out for you name.  Or better yet.... pick a name that fits the genre and not something that is obviously a phrase just to see how long you can get away with it.  Not saying I agree with the naming policy but its not like we are not aware of the rules. <p>Tagarth Stormhammer<BR>Templar of the 56th Summer<BR><img src=http://frontpage.home.com/briancarr00/images/Tagarth56.jpg></br>Never give in--never, never, never, never, in nothing great</br> or small, large or petty, never give in except to convictions</br> of honour and good sense."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoelnhazapet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oeln Hazapet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 249<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/31/02 3:32:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is &quot;Hazapet&quot; a sentence? (please read)</span><hr size=1> Ok, I guess youre all right. Oeln Hazapet is a sentence. I was just waiting for the &quot;If I speel a word wrong in a sentence does that not make it a sentence?&quot; statement. Oeln haz a pet is a sentence... This stinks... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showMessageRange?topicID=615.topic&start=21&stop=22>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showPrevMessage?topicID=615.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showNextMessage?topicID=615.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=20